.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_tasks.md:5:**MVP boundary:** tasks 01-16 implement the autonomy kernel. Tasks 17-18 prepare and execute QA. Post-MVP network evolution, broad memory scopes, self-correction telemetry, eval/replay, and broad web visibility remain follow-up TechSpecs unless explicitly pulled into scope later.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_techspec.md:45:Keeps the local autonomy MVP focused: task-run coordination channel binding, channel discovery metadata, peer status, handoff when needed, and enough peer/channel inspection for agents and the coordinator to route work. Cross-daemon swarm, leader election, and broad contract-net behavior remain out of scope for the MVP.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_techspec.md:49:Makes coordination outcomes durable and useful: agent/session provenance, session summaries, recall provenance, workflow correlation, loop detection, budget/iteration circuit breakers, and a basic eval/replay harness. Memory improvements start with provenance and session summaries before adding broad peer/channel scope extraction.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_techspec.md:453:| `internal/network` | modified in MVP | Minimal channel discovery, task-run coordination channel metadata, status, handoff, reply simplification. Medium risk. | Add only task/run correlation metadata and MVP message kinds; defer multi-home, contract-net, vote/react/escalate, and cross-daemon routing. |
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_techspec.md:499:- Eval/replay harness can replay a recorded autonomy flow without live provider calls.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_techspec.md:531:11. **Post-MVP network evolution** - depends on MVP validation. Add multi-home sessions, richer peer negotiation, contract-net verbs, and broader handoff/mention semantics only after local autonomy proves the needed wire shape.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_techspec.md:534:14. **Post-MVP eval/replay harness** - depends on MVP validation. Add recorded ACP/session trajectories, YAML cases, replay fixtures, and deterministic assertions under a dedicated ADR/TechSpec.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_techspec.md:682:Likelihood: medium. Mitigation: local autonomy comes first; cross-daemon swarm, election, and broad contract-net semantics stay out of MVP.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_techspec.md:695:- [ADR-002: Agent-Facing CLI Before Built-In MCP Tools](adrs/adr-002.md) - Make identity-implicit CLI/UDS verbs the first agent control surface; MCP tools can mirror them later.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/_techspec.md:700:- [ADR-007: Minimal Network Evolution for Local Autonomy](adrs/adr-007.md) - Add only the channel/status/handoff pieces needed for local autonomy before broader cross-daemon swarm work.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-001.md:15:The design must avoid speculative features that do not unlock local autonomous operation, including cross-daemon swarm coordination, leader election, vector memory, signed skill supply chain, generic runtime tool execution, and Prometheus/webhook integrations. The design must also preserve manual task creation and manual session startup as first-class paths.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-001.md:31:The first implementation wave will prioritize local daemon autonomy through the kernel steps: contracts/config, hook taxonomy, Situation Surface, Agent Kernel CLI, task claim/lease, scheduler sweep/notify, safe spawn, and coordinator bootstrap. Network evolution, broad memory expansion, self-correction beyond minimal counters, eval/replay, and web visibility are follow-on TechSpecs unless explicitly pulled into scope later.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-001.md:46:- **Description**: Include every proposal from the analysis, including cross-daemon swarm, contract-net, multi-home sessions, generic tools, vector memory, and advanced observability.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-011.md:39:Broad web visibility remains post-MVP: no new `web/src/systems/coordinator` module, no autonomy sidebar item, no live lease dashboard, no spawn lineage tree visualization, no idle-agent registry view, no eval/replay UI, no coordinator config GUI, and no marketing site rewrite.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-007.md:13:The autonomy analysis proposed many network protocol improvements, including multi-home sessions, contract-net verbs, mentions, voting, reactions, escalation, and cross-daemon coordination. The approved scope focuses on local daemon autonomy first while retaining network affordances that help agents coordinate.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-007.md:24:- Defer contract-net, multi-home sessions, vote/react/escalate/offer/accept/decline, and complex mention routing.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-007.md:49:- Keeps local autonomy independent from cross-daemon swarm design.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-002.md:1:# ADR-002: Agent-Facing CLI Before Built-In MCP Tools
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-002.md:19:Stabilize an agent-facing CLI and UDS/API contract before introducing built-in MCP tools. The CLI will support identity inference from session environment, stable `-o json` output, `-o jsonl` streaming for wait/subscribe commands, and canonical commands such as `agh me context`, `agh ch reply`, `agh ch recv --wait`, and `agh task next/heartbeat/complete/fail/release`. `agh task next` returns the coordination channel for channel-bound runs, and `agh ch` is the operational communication surface for those runs. Avoid aliases such as `done` or `pass` in the MVP so each lifecycle concept has one command name.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-002.md:21:Built-in MCP tools may later mirror the same contract, but they are not part of the first autonomy implementation.
.compozy/tasks/autonomous/adrs/adr-002.md:43:- Establishes one stable contract before adding MCP mirrors.
